TurtleBot3-Burger Progress
Since we got the TB3-B:
Got ROS Noetic running on TB3-B before realizing that ROS Kinetic offers more support for it. 
Switched to ROS Kinetic. Also put Ubunutu 16.04 onto an external SSD in order to have a mobile ROS platform. So far it has worked well.
Have started Lidar, Camera(OpenCV), and Autonomous Mapping.
Got TurtleBot4 and wanted to use both together, however TB3-B uses ROS1 Kinetic and TB4 uses ROS2 Humble. To fix this implemented a ROS1-ROS2 bridge. 
There were significant issues at first, most noteably was time. Since TB3-B and TB4 were not time synced, they could not operate autonomously together.
To fix this I set the TB3-B's ntp(Network Time Protocal) as the TB4's RPI4. So whatever time the TB4 is using is automatically the time that the TB3-B is using.
After this was fixed the robots were able to use syncronous SLAM but the RPLIDAR's were not working together. After troubleshooting I discovered that both of the Lidars were set as the primary. After setting the TB3-B's Lidar as the secondary, (because TB4 has a newer RPLIDAR), they synced and worked properly.
